  "prompt": "Can I use a same mobile number for two accounts in sbi for internet banking?",
  "response": "Generally, no. Each SBI internet banking account requires a unique mobile number for registration and authentication purposes. This is done for security reasons and to ensure proper identification of account holders.\n\nHere are some key points:\n\n1. Typically, one mobile number can be linked to only one SBI internet banking account.\n\n2. If you want to register another account, you'll need to use a different mobile number.\n\n3. You can contact your SBI branch or customer service to confirm the exact policy or explore alternative options.\n\n4. If you have multiple accounts, you might be able to link them under a single internet banking login, but each would still require its own unique contact details.\n\nRecommendation:\n- Use different mobile numbers for different accounts\n- If you don't have another mobile number, consider using a family member's number or alternative contact methods\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to:\n- Contact SBI customer support\n- Visit a local SBI branch\n- Check the official SBI website for current policies",
